<p>When selecting a solar installer in Fresno, prioritize companies with proper California licensing (C-46 solar contractor license), strong local presence, and extensive experience in the Central Valley's unique conditions. Look for installers who offer comprehensive warranties covering equipment (typically 20-25 years for panels, 10-12 years for inverters) and workmanship (minimum 10 years). Reputable Fresno solar companies should provide detailed energy production estimates based on your specific roof orientation and shading conditions, offer multiple financing options, and have solid Better Business Bureau ratings with local references. Given Fresno's extreme heat, ensure your installer uses high-quality mounting systems designed for thermal expansion and has experience with the city's permitting process. The best installers will also help you navigate PG&E's interconnection requirements and assist with rebate applications.</p>

